<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idec0e15ba-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70903"><num value="70903">§ 70903.</num><heading> International Space Station research</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e15bb-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70903/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> carry out a program of microgravity research consistent with <ref href="/us/usc/t51/s40904">section 40904 of this title</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e15bc-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70903/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> consider the need for a life sciences centrifuge and any associated holding facilities.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idec0e15bd-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/314/s3">Pub. L. 111–314, § 3</ref>, <date date="2010-12-18">Dec. 18, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3436">124 Stat. 3436</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
